result.formatted_address: 513 Nathan Rd, Yau Ma Tei, Hong Kong
result.name: Yee Shun Milk Company -Yau Ma Tei

reviews.text: The milk pudding was delicious! I tried the ginger and the coffee one. The sandwiches though...?? They were made with plain white bread (not toasted, using processed cheese slices and not much flavour). It was also expensive for what we got! I recommend going to the Australian Dairy Company instead!! The Australian Dairy Company uses more eggs in their sandwiches, toasts then, and uses better cheese. Australian Dairy Company Gad more options and their dishes are more delicious.

Their milk pudding is quite good. However, I felt the service is a bit dishonest. I kept asking for a breakfast set (I was there around 9 a.m.) but their reply was they don't serve it (when you clearly can see other tables eating them). I ended up ordering three different dishes which cost me $150 HKD, which is a bit too much for a simple breakfast meal here. KNOW WHAT TO ORDER BEFORE YOU GO!

Food was not bad yet staff attitude was poor - The attitude of the cashier was extremely poor and insulting.  She actually told me off when I enquired the price of a cold beverage.  Also I didn’t feel welcome when I went in this afternoon, I told 2 attendants on separate occasions that i was alone, they didn’t respond nor guide me to a seat.  Finally I saw an empty seat and sat down.  I was not looking for 5-star service here but expected basic courtesy and service.

First the good, the original milk pudding is nice, good texture and slight sweetness. We also had the red bean pudding, it was good but too sweet.

However, the cheese and ham sandwich was very bad. Bread was hard and stale, had a small piece of ham and a processed cheese slice for $25, you must be kidding! 😂

My pork and egg sandwich was also mediocre, the pork had no flavour and bread was also stale.

Our milk puddings were literally thrown on the table. The staff speak a little English and mandarin when ordering, but after the food is thrown in front of you and you need their attention they just wave they arms in the air and only speak Cantonese.

Should have read other reviews more carefully, don't waste your money here. $140 for 2 of us and we are still hungry. Would have done better at McDonald's. 

The prices are ridiculous and you will be abused by the staff for the privilege of dining here. 😫

Seeing the good reviews on google, my family and I went there to have a taste of the pudding from this infamous place. There was not many people dining there at about 8 plus when we were there. A lady handed us a menu and stood at the edge, impatiently waiting for our order. We ordered 4 items. The lady ticked them on the order sheet. When it came, our milk puddings were thrown on the table. However, it turned out that the 3 of the orders were wrong. Out of which, one was supposed to be a cold dessert but turned out hot. We asked the waitress if she had given us the wrong order. She confidently said we had told her that she had taken the right order. Abruptly, she then took the order slip and amended our order even though she denied her mistake. The cashier was rude upon payment.

The prices are ridiculous. Super disappointing. Went in happy and excited, but extremely poor experience at the end. Will never visit again.

食物不錯吃
但價格不便宜
一個燉奶就要36蚊
双皮奶奶味很濃，其他普通，還是澳洲牛奶好吃

跟澳洲牛奶公司齊名的店，賣的東西其實就是香港最常見的那些食物，選擇很多，味道普通。
最出名的東西大概是燉奶。

不過，這幾年價格越來越驚人，一碗雙皮燉奶要價港幣36（2019/06）。

result.formatted_address: 506 Lockhart Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Yee Shun Milk Company - Causeway Bay

reviews.text:
Quality is way better than the Jordan location.  Expensive but taste and smoothness is very good. 

Expectation should be tailored to the fact that this is a fast type of restaurant where you are expected to order within minutes of sitting, leave when you're done and not being outside food in. Sharing tables is common and to be expected so if it's a busy time you should expect to have to sit on one side with enough room for another person or group of strangers to join you.

Very tasty pudding but the cost is very expensive for what is a small portion size and essentially milk and sugar... The service was average and ambiance lacking.. definitely worth trying the hot steamed milk with ginger... If not for the price I would return often... Also.. apparently there is usually a queue which if that is true.. I wouldn't not wait longer than 20mins..

Ordered steam egg & steam milk. 
The steam milk was topped with red bean paste as recommended by the waitress. 
This is when things go wrong. When the steam milk arrived, we took one spoonful and found that it tasted like YOGHURT? Haven't tried this before, we found the taste a little bit funky. Then took a few more spoonful and detected that, the red bean paste if off,hence the sourness. 
We did not finished it.

Food was nice but extremely bad staff. Being shouted by the waitress because I have a almost finished bobble tea on the table, also got shouted again because me and my friend were sitting in front of each other instead of next to each other. Cashier attitude is shocking as if I’m the one own her money. After paying, being chased at outside by the waitress shouted at my face that I didn’t pay.
Terrible service and unfriendly waitress. Ginger mixed milk is just ordinary but very overpriced

reviews.text: 적당히 달달하고 맛있었습니다. 저는 푸딩을 별로 안좋아하는데도 불구하고 궁금해서 먹어봤는데 시원하고 맛있었습니다. 아이스밀크티도 먹었는데 되게 진하고 맛있습니다. 처음 나올때는 미지근하니 저어가면서 얼음이 다 녹으면 마셔야 시원하고 좋습니다. 한자메뉴판밖에 안보여서 사진 보여주면서 영어메뉴 얘기하니까 잘 알아들으시고 제대로 주문한 메뉴가 나왔습니다. 시원한 푸딩은 미리 만들어놓은거라 바로 나와서 금방먹고 나왔어요
